es\n***[[Assamese people|Indigenous Assamese people]]\n*****[[Tripuri people|Tripuri]] (Borok): [[Tripura]], [[North-East India]]\n****[[Konyak languages|Konyak]] peoples\n*****[[Nocte]]: Tirap, [[Arunachal Pradesh]], [[North-East India]]\n***[[Kukish]] peoples\n****[[Karbi people|Karbi]]: [[Karbi Anglong]], [[Assam]], [[North-East-India]]\n****[[Mizo people|Mizo]] (Mizo hnam): [[Mizoram]], [[North-East India]]\n****[[Naga (people)|Naga]]: [[Nagaland]], [[North-East India]]\n***[[Raji-Raute]] peoples\n****[[Raute people|Raute]]: [[Nepal]], [[North India]]\n**[[Digaro languages|Digaro]] peoples\n***[[Mishmi people|Mishmi]]: [[Arunachal Pradesh]], [[North-East India]]\n**[[Jumma people]] (a collective term for several peoples)\n***[[Chakma people|Chakma]]: [[Bangladesh]], [[Arunachal Pradesh]] - [[North-East India]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples of Sikkim]]: India\n***[[Sino-Tibetan peoples]]\n****[[Bodish languages|Bodish]] peoples\n*****[[Bhutia]] (Denzongpa)\n****[[Lepcha people|Lepcha]] (R\u00f3ng \u0294\u00e1g\u00edt/R\u00f3ngkup/M\u00fatunc\u00ed R\u00f3ngkup Rumkup)\n****[[Meitei people|Meitei]]: [[Manipur]], [[North-East India]]\n*[[Dravidian peoples]]\n**[[South Dravidian]] peoples\n***[[Giraavaru people|Giraavaru]]: [[Maldives]]\n*[[Burusho people|Burusho]]: [[Hunza District|Hunza]] and [[Chitral]] districts, [[Gilgit-Baltistan]], Northern [[Pakistan]]\n*Indo-European peoples\n**[[Iranian peoples]]\n***[[Pashtuns]]: southern Afghanistan and Northwest Pakistan\n***[[Baloch people|Baloch]]: southeastern Iran, southwest Pakistan\n**[[Indo-Aryan peoples]]\n***[[Dard people|Dard]]: [[Dardistan]], [[Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa]], [[Gilgit-Baltistan]], Northern [[Pakistan]]\n****[[Kalash people|Kalasha of Chitral]] (Ka\u013aa\u015ba): Ancient pre-Muslim polytheistic pagan ethnic minority in [[Chitral District]], [[Northern Pakistan]]\n****[[Shina people|Shina]]: [[Gilgit-Baltistan]], Northern [[Pakistan]]\n****[[Kashmiri Pandit|Kashmiri Hindus]]: [[India]]\n***[[Sindhi people|Sindhi]]: [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]], [[India]]\n***[[Bengali people|Bengali]]: [[India]], [[Bangladesh]]\n***[[Gujarati people|Gujarati]]: [[India]]\n*[[Sino-Tibetan peoples]]\n**[[Lolo-Burmese]] peoples\n***[[Burmish]] peoples\n****[[Marma people|Marma]]: [[Bangladesh]]\n**[[Meitei people]]: [[Manipur]] and neighboring states of India, [[Bangladesh]], [[Myanmur]]\n*[[Vedda people|Vedda]] (Wanniyala-Aetto): [[Sri Lanka]]\n*[[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]]: [[Sri Lanka]]\n*[[Sri Lankan Tamil people|Sri Lankan Tamil]]: [[Sri Lanka]]\n*[[Maldivians|Dhivehi]]: [[Maldives]]\n\n===== Southeast Asia =====\n====== [[Mainland Southeast Asia|Mainland Southeast Asia (Indochinese Peninsula)]] ======\n[[File:Wa villagers 00.jpg|thumb|A [[Wa people|Wa]] woman carrying her child]]\n[[File:2010 Karen girls Khun Yuam district.jpg|thumb|[[S'gaw Karen]] girls of [[Khun Yuam District]], [[Mae Hong Son Province]], Thailand]]\n[[File:Akha laos 11 03d.jpg|thumb|[[Akha people|Akha]] girl in [[Laos]]]]\n[[File:Yi-Minority.JPG|thumb|[[Yi people|Yi]]/Nuosu women]]\n[[File:2007 1202 Tai Dam woman Yunnan.jpg|thumb|A Tai Dam lady in Laomeng village, [[Jinping Miao, Yao, and Dai Autonomous County]], [[Yunnan Province]], China.]]\n\n*[[Austroasiatic]] peoples\n**[[Aslian]] peoples\n***[[Senoi]] (Sengoi/Sng'oi) (a people of the ethnic groups called by the generic word [[Orang Asli]] - Original People): in [[Peninsular Malaysia]])\n**[[Khmer Krom]]: of [[Vietnam]]\n**[[Khmuic]] groups:\n***[[Khmu people|Khmu]] (Kmm\u0325u\u0294/Kmm\u00fa\u0294): [[Thailand]] and [[Laos]]\n***[[Mlabri people|Mlabri]]: Northern [[Thailand]] and [[Laos]]\n***[[Pray people|Pray]]: [[Thailand]] and [[Laos]]\n**[[Palaungic]] peoples\n***[[Wa people|Wa]] (V\u0101x): One of the [[hill people|hill tribes]] of [[Myanmar]] and China's [[Yunnan Province]]\n***[[Zo people|Zomi]] (Zo Pau): One of the indigenous people in Southeast Asia. The word Zomi is the collective name given to many tribes who traced their descent from a common ancestor. Through history they have been known under various appellation, such as\u2014Chin, Kuki and Mizo\u2014but the expression was disliked by them, and they insist that the term was a misnomer given by others and by which they have been recorded in certain documents designate their ancient origins as a race.\n*[[Austronesian peoples]]\n**[[Malayo-Polynesian]] peoples\n***[[Chamic]] peoples\n****[[Cham people (Asia)|Cham]] (Chams/Urang Campa): of [[Vietnam]] and [[Cambodia]]\n***[[Proto-Malay]] (a people of the ethnic groups called by the generic word [[Orang Asli]] - Original People): in [[Peninsular Malaysia]]\n***[[Moken people|Moken]]: in [[Myanmar]], and [[Thailand]]\n*[[Hmong-Mien]] peoples\n**[[Hmong people|Hmong]]: subgroups of [[Thailand]], [[Myanmar]], [[Laos]], [[Vietnam]] and a Chinese minority\n*[[Montagnards (people)|Montagnards]] (Degar): an umbrella term for several Pre-Vietnamese peoples that dwell in the plateaus and mountains of the southern regions of [[Vietnam]]\n**[[Austroasiatic]] peoples\n***Bahnaric peoples\n****North Bahnaric peoples\n*****[[Sedang people|Sedang]]: [[Vietnam]]\n****Central Bahnaric peoples\n*****[[Bahnar people|Bahnar]]: [[Central Highland provinces]] of [[Gia Lai]] and [[Kon Tum]], as well as the coastal provinces of [[B\u00ecnh \u0110\u1ecbnh]] and [[Ph\u00fa Y\u00ean]] ([[Vietnam]])\n*****[[Mnong people|Mnong]]: [[Cambodia]] and [[Vietnam]]\n*****[[Stieng people|Stieng]]: [[Cambodia]] and [[Vietnam]] \n***[[Katuic peoples]]\n****Katu\n*****[[Katu people|Katu]]: [[Vietnam]] and [[Laos]]\n****West\n*****[[Bru people|Bru]] (Bruu): [[Thailand]], [[Laos]], [[India]] and [[Vietnam]]\n**[[Austronesian peoples]]\n***[[Malayo-Polynesian]] peoples\n****[[Chamic]] peoples\n*****Highlands Chamic peoples\n******Rade-Jarai\n*******[[Jarai people|Jarai]]: [[Central Highlands (Vietnam)|Central Highlands]] of [[Vietnam]], as well as in the Northeast Province of [[Ratanakiri]] ([[Cambodia]])\n*******[[Rhade people|Rhade]]: Southern [[Vietnam]]\n******Chru\u2013Northern\n*******Northern Cham\n********[[Raglai people|Raglai]]: in [[Kh\u00e1nh H\u00f2a Province]] of [[South Central Coast]], and [[Ninh Thu\u1eadn Province]] in the Southeast region of [[Vietnam]]\n*[[Negrito]]:\n**[[Mani people|Mani]] (Maniq): Far Southern [[Thailand]]\n**[[Semang]] (a group of several peoples of the ethnic groups called by the generic word [[Orang Asli]] - Original People): [[Peninsular Malaysia]]\n**[[Batek people|Batek]]: [[Peninsular Malaysia]]\n*[[Sino-Tibetan peoples]]\n**[[Karenic]] peoples\n***[[Karen people|Karen]] (Per Ploan Poe/Ploan/Pwa Ka Nyaw/Kanyaw): an alliance of [[hill tribes]] of [[Myanmar]] and [[Thailand]]\n**[[Lolo-Burmese]] peoples\n***[[Akha people|Akha]] a.k.a. Aini or Aini-Akha: One of the hill tribes of [[Thailand]], [[Laos]], [[Burma]] and China's [[Yunnan Province]]\n***[[Lahu people|Lahu]] (Ladhulsi/Kawzhawd): One of the [[hill tribes]] of [[Thailand]], [[Myanmar]], [[Laos]] and [[Yunnan]].\n***[[Lisu people|Lisu]]: One of the [[hill tribes]] of [[Myanmar]], [[Thailand]], [[Arunachal Pradesh]], India & [[Yunnan]] and [[Sichuan]], China\n***[[Rakhine people|Rakhine]] (R\u0259kh\u00e0in l\u00f9mj\u00f3): [[Rakhine State|Arakan]] in [[Myanmar]]\n***[[Yi people|Yi]] (Nuosu/Nisu/Sani/Axi/Lolo): a group of several related peoples in Southern [[China]], mainly in [[Yunnan Province]].\n**[[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]] peoples\n***[[Intha people|Intha]]: [[Inle Lake]] of [[Myanmar]]\n*[[Tai peoples]]: [[China]], [[Vietnam]], [[Myanmar]], [[Laos]] and [[Thailand]]\n**[[Southwestern Tai]] peoples\n***[[Kh\u00fcn]] (Thai Kh\u00fcn)\n***[[Phu Thai language|Phu Thai]] \n***[[Tai Dam people|Tai Dam]]: [[China]], Northwest [[Vietnam]], [[Laos]], [[Thailand]]\n***[[Lu people|Tai Lu]]: [[China]] ([[Xishuangbanna Dai Autonomous Prefecture|Xishuangbanna]]), [[Laos]], Northern [[Thailand]], [[Myanmar]], and [[Vietnam]] ([[Lai Ch\u00e2u Province]])\n***[[Tai N\u00fca]]\n\n====== [[Maritime Southeast Asia]] ([[Malay Archipelago]]) ======\n[[File:KgKuaiKandazon Sabah Monsopiad-Cultural-Village-23.jpg|thumb|A [[Murut people|Murut]] man (a member of one of the [[Dayak people|Dayak]] ethnicities) in Monsopiad Cultural Village, Kg. Kuai Kandazon, [[Penampang]], [[Sabah]], [[Borneo]] Island]]\n[[File:Ati woman.jpg|thumb|[[Ati (tribe)|Ati]] woman, the [[Philippines]], 2007<ref>\"[http://www.unhcr.org/refworld/country,,,COUNTRYPROF,PHL,4562d8cf2,4954ce2123,0.html World Directory of Minorities and Indigenous Peoples \u2013 Philippines: Overview, 2007]\", UNHCR | Refworld.</ref> The [[Negrito]]s were the earliest inhabitants of Southeast Asia.<ref>{{cite journal|pmid=1605316|title=Negritos, Australian Aborigines, and the proto-sundadont dental pattern: The basic populations in East Asia|year=1992|last1=Hanihara|first1=T|volume=88|issue=2|pages=183\u201396|doi=10.1002/ajpa.1330880206|journal=American Journal of Physical Anthropology }}</ref>]]\n\n*[[Austroasiatic]] peoples\n**[[Nicobarese|Nicobarese people]] ([[Nicobarese people|Holchu]]): [[Nicobar Islands]], [[India]]\n**[[Shompen people]] (Kalay-Keyet): [[Nicobar Islands]], India\n*[[Austronesian peoples]]\n**[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] peoples\n***[[Barito people]]s\n****[[Sama-Bajau people|Bajau]] (Sama/Samah/Samal): [[Borneo]] and the [[Sulu Archipelago]] ([[Malaysia]], [[Indonesia]], [[Philippines]])\n***[[Dayak people|Dayak]]: [[Borneo]], ([[Malaysia]] and [[Indonesia]])\n***[[Northwest Sumatra\u2013Barrier Islands languages|Northwest Sumatra\u2013Barrier Islands]] peoples\n****[[Mentawai language|Mentawai]] peoples\n*****[[Mentawai people|Mentawai]]: [[Mentawai Islands]], [[Indonesia]]\n*****[[Sakuddei]]: [[Siberut Island]] and [[Mentawai Islands]], [[Indonesia]]\n***[[Malay peoples|Malayic peoples]]\n****[[Orang Laut]] and [[Orang Seletar]]: [[Malaysia]] and [[Singapore]]\n****[[Proto-Malay]] (Melayu asli/Melayu purba): [[Malaysia]]\n***[[North Bornean languages|North Bornean]] peoples\n****[[Penan]]: [[Sarawak]], [[Malaysia]]\n****[[Lun Bawang]]: [[Sarawak]], [[Malaysia]]\n***[[Philippine languages|Philippine]] peoples\n****[[Igorot]] (Ifugao:Ipugao; Benguet:Ibaloi,Kankanaey; Mountain Province:Bontoc; Kalinga:Kiangan; Abra:Itneg; Apayao:Isneg):<ref>{{cite book |last=Agpaoa |first=Joshua C. |year=2013 |title=Design Motifs of the Northern Philippine Textiles}}</ref> [[Cordillera Administrative Region|Cordillera mountains]] in [[Luzon]] in the [[Philippines]]\n****[[Lumad people|Lumad]] (Katawhang Lumad): [[Mindanao]] in the [[Philippines]]\n****[[Mangyan]]: [[Mindoro]] in the Philippines\n****[[Moro people|Moro]]: [[Mindanao]] and [[Sulu archipelago]] in the [[Philippines]]\n*****[[Tausug people|Tausug]] (Taus\u016bg/Suluk/Sulug)\n*****[[Maguindanao people|Maguindanao]]\n*****[[Maranao people|Maranao]] (Iranon/Iranun)\n****[[Ethnic Groups of Palawan|Tribes of Palawan]]: [[Palawan]], [[Philippines]]\n*[[Orang Rimba people|Orang Rimba]] (Orang Batin Sembilan/Orang Rimba/Anak Dalam/Kubu): [[Sumatra]], [[Indonesia]]\n*[[Lubu people|Lubu]]: [[Sumatra]], [[Indonesia]]\n*[[Negrito]]:\n**[[Andamanese]], in the [[Andaman Islands]], which include:\n***[[Great Andamanese]]: formerly at least 10 distinct groups living throughout [[Great Andaman]], now confined to a single community on [[Strait Island]], Andaman Is.\n***[[Jangil|Jangil (Rutland Jarawa)]]: now extinct, formerly of [[Rutland Island]], Andamans\n***[[Jarawa (Andaman Islands)|Jarawa]]: [[South Andaman]] and [[Middle Andaman]]\n***[[Onge people|Onge]] (\u00d6nge): [[Little Andaman]], [[Andaman Islands]]\n***[[Sentinelese people|Sentinelese]] (?): [[North Sentinel Island]], [[Andaman Islands]]\n**[[Aeta]]: [[Luzon]], [[Philippines]]\n**[[Ati (tribe)|Ati]]: [[Panay]], [[Philippines]]\n**[[Batak people (Philippines)|Batak]]: [[Palawan]], [[Philippines]]\n*[[Pribumi (Native Indonesians)]]: of [[Indonesia]]\n\n{{See also|Indigenous peoples of the Philippines}}\n\n===== East Asia =====\n====== Western China ======\n*[[Tibetans|Tibetan]] peoples\n*[[Uyghurs|Uyghur]] peoples\n\n====== North China ======\n*[[Tungusic peoples|Tungusic]] peoples\n**[[Northern Tungusic]] peoples\n***[[Nanai people|Nanai]] (Hezhen/Nanai/Hezhe/Golds/Samagir): [[Heilongjiang Province|Heilongjiang]] in China, [[Khabarovsk Krai]] and [[Primorsky Krai]] in Russia\n***[[Oroqen people|Oroqen]]: Far Northern [[China]]\n**[[Southern Tungusic]] peoples\n***[[Manchu people|Manchu]] (Manju/Manchu people): [[Manchuria]], northeast [[China]]\n\n====== South China ======\n[[File:Chine Miao \u00e0 cornes9317a.jpg|thumb|[[Miao people|Miao]] ([[Hmong people|Hmong]]) girls in China]]\n[[File:taiwan bunun dancer.jpg|thumb|[[Bunun people|Bunun]] dancer]]\n\n*[[Hmong-Mien]] peoples\n**[[Miao people|Miao]]: Southern [[China]] (provinces of [[Guizhou]], [[Yunnan]], [[Sichuan]], [[Hubei]], [[Hunan]], [[Guangxi]], [[Guangdong]] and [[Hainan]]), [[Myanmar]], northern [[Vietnam]], [[Laos]] and [[Thailand]]\n**[[Hmong people|Hmong]]: [[Southern China]], [[Vietnam]] and [[Laos]]\n**[[Yao people|Yao]] (Mien): Southern [[China]] (provinces [[Hunan]], [[Guangdong]], [[Guangxi]], [[Guizhou]], and [[Yunnan]])\n\n====== Taiwan ======\n{{Main|Taiwanese indigenous peoples|List of indigenous peoples of Taiwan}}\n\n*Indigenous peoples of the island of [[Taiwan]]\n**[[Amis people|Amis]] (Pangcah)\n**[[Sakizaya people|Sakizaya]]\n**[[Bunun people|Bunun]]\n**[[Kavalan people|Kavalan]] (Kebalan; Kbaran)\n**[[Atayal people|Atayal]] (Tayal; Tayan)\n**[[Saisiyat people|Saisiyat]] (Say-Siyat)\n**[[Seediq people|Seediq]]\n**[[Truku people|Truku]] (Taroko)\n**[[Thao people|Thao]] (Ngan)\n**[[Paiwan people|Paiwan]] (Payuan)\n**[[Puyuma people|Puyuma]] (Pinuyumayan)\n**[[Rukai people|Rukai]] (Drekay)\n**[[Tsou people|Tsou]] (Cou)\n**[[Yami people|Yami]] (Tao)\n**[[Saaroa people|Hla'alua]] (Saaroa)\n**[[Kanakanavu people|Kanakanavu]]\n\n====== Japan ======\n*[[Ainu people|Ainu]] (Aynu): [[Hokkaido]], Japan and (until the end of World War II) on [[Sakhalin]] Island, Russia\n*[[Japonic languages|Japonic]] peoples\n**[[Ryukyuan people|Ryukyuans]] (Ruuchuu Minzuku): Old [[Ry\u016bky\u016b Kingdom]], now [[Japan]]\n\n\n==== Europe ====\n===== Eastern Europe =====\n[[File:Gagauz-children.jpg|thumb|[[Gagauz people|Gagauz]] old and young people.]]\n[[File:Erzya women.jpg|thumb|[[Mordvin people|Mordvin]] women of [[Penza Oblast]] dressed in traditional costumes.]]\n\n*[[Turkic peoples]]\n**Common Turks\n***[[Kipchaks|Kipchak Turks]] ([[Kipchak language|Northwestern Common Turkic]] peoples)\n****[[Bashkirs]] (Ba\u015fqorttar): [[Bashkir Republic]], [[European Russia]]\n****[[Crimean Karaites]] (Qrymqaraylar): [[Crimean Peninsula]] in Southern [[Ukraine]]\n****[[Crimean Tatars]] (Q\u0131r\u0131mtatarlar): [[Crimean Peninsula]] in Southern [[Ukraine]]\n****[[Volga Tatars]] (Tatarlar): [[Tatarstan]], [[European Russia]]\n***[[Oghuz Turks]] ([[Southwestern Common Turkic]] peoples)\n****[[Gagauz people|Gagauz]] (Gagauzlar): [[Gagauzia]], [[Moldova]]\n**[[Oghur Turks]]\n***[[Chuvash people|Chuvash]] (Ch\u0103v\u0430sh): [[Chuvash Republic]], [[Russia]]\n*[[Finno-Ugric peoples]]\n***[[Baltic Finns]]\n****[[Izhorians]] (I\u017eoralaizet/Inkeroine/Izhora/Izhoralaine/Karjalain/Maav\u00e4ki): Northwest of [[Russia]]\n****[[Karelians]] (Karjalai\u017eet): Northwest of [[Russia]]\n****[[Livonians]] (Raandalist/Kalamied/Liiv\u00f5d/Liib\u00f5d/Liivnikad/Liivlist): Far Northern [[Courland]] peninsula, [[Latvia]]\n****[[Setos]] (Setok\u00f5s\u00f5q): [[Setomaa]] - Far Southeastern [[Estonia]], southern border region between [[Estonia]] and [[Russia]], East [[V\u00f5ru County]] and Northwest [[Pskov Oblast]], southwest of [[Chudskoye Lake|Chudskoye-Pskov/Peipus]] Lake.\n****[[Vepsians|Veps]] (Vepslaine/Bepslaane/L\u00fcdinik/L\u00fcdilaine): [[Republic of Karelia]], Northwest of [[Russia]]\n***[[Permians]]\n****[[Komi peoples|Komi]] (Komiyas): [[Komi Republic]] in Northeast of [[European Russia]]\n****[[Udmurt people|Udmurts]] (Udmurt'yos): [[Udmurt Republic]] in Northeast of [[European Russia]]\n***[[Sami people|Sami]] (S\u00e1mi/Saami): [[S\u00e1pmi]], Northern and central [[Norway]], Northern [[Sweden]], Northern [[Finland]] and [[Kola peninsula]] in the Northwest of [[Russia]]\n***[[Volga Finns]]\n****[[Mari people|Mari]]: Middle [[Volga]], [[European Russia]]\n****[[Mordvins]] (Erzyat/Mokshet): [[European Russia]]\n*****[[Erzyans]] (Erzyat)\n*****[[Moksha]] (Mokshet)\n*[[Samoyedic peoples]]\n***[[Samoyedic languages|North Samoyedic]] peoples\n****[[Nenets people|Nenets]] (Neney Neneche) : Northeastern part of [[European Russia]]\n\n===== Northern and western Europe =====\n{{Main|Sami people}}\n\n* The [[Sami people|Sami]] are indigenous to [[S\u00e1pmi]] in northern [[Norway]], [[Sweden]], [[Finland]] and the [[Kola peninsula]] in [[Russia]]. They are legally recognised as indigenous peoples in all four countries.<ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=L1GFCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA424|last=Johansson|first=Peter|title=Handbook of Indigenous Peoples' Rights|editor-last=Short|editor-first=Damien|editor-last2=Lennox|editor-first2=Corinne|date=2016-02-05|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781136313868|location=London|pages=424\u2013442|language=en|chapter=Indigenous self-determination in the Nordic countries: the Sami, and the Inuit of Greenland}}</ref><ref name=\"Osherenko\">{{cite web|title=Indigenous rights in Russia: Is title to land essential for cultural survival? |last=Osherenko |first=Gail |date=April 1, 2001 |website=Georgetown International Environmental Law Review |url=http://www.allbusiness.com/legal/international-law/1112279-1.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110511104207/http://www.allbusiness.com/legal/international-law/1112279-1.html |archivedate=May 11, 2011 }}</ref>\n* In the [[United Kingdom]], [[crofters]] have asked to be designated as indigenous peoples of the [[Scottish Highlands]]. The [[Government of the United Kingdom|UK government]] does not officially recognise any indigenous peoples within the country.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/this-britain/crofters-fight-for-rights-of-indigenous-people-811791.html |title = Crofters fight for rights of indigenous people|date = 2008-04-19}}</ref>\n\n== Americas ==\n[[Americas]] is the supercontinent comprising North and South America, and associated islands.\n{{Main|Classification of indigenous peoples of the Americas}}\n\nList of peoples by geographical and ethnolinguistic grouping:\n\n=== North America ===\n[[North America]] includes all of the continent and islands east of the [[Bering Strait]] and north of the [[Isthmus of Panama]]; it includes [[Greenland]], [[Canada]], [[United States]], [[Mexico]], Central American and Caribbean countries. However a distinction can be made between a broader [[North America]] and a narrower [[Northern America]] and [[Middle America (Americas)|Middle America]] due to ethnic and cultural characteristics.\n\n{{Main|List of First Nations peoples|Federally recognized tribes|Indigenous peoples of Mexico}}\n\n*[[Indigenous peoples in North America]] by Country\n**[[Aboriginal peoples in Canada]]\n***[[First Nations]]\n***[[Inuit]]\n***[[M\u00e9tis]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples in the United States]]\n***[[Alaska Natives]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples of Mexico]]\n*[[Indigenous peoples in North America]] by native cultural regions\n\n==== Arctic ====\n[[File:Iglulik Clothing 1999-07-18.jpg|thumb|Two [[Inuit]] women in traditional [[amauti]] (packing parkas)]]\n\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the North American Arctic}}\n\n*[[Ancient Beringian]] - [[Siberia]] and [[Alaska]]\n*[[Eskimo]]\u2013[[Aleut]]\n**[[Aleut]] (Unangax): [[Aleutian Islands]] and [[Kamchatka Krai]]\n**[[Eskimo peoples|Eskimo]]/[[Eskimo peoples|Yupit-Inuit]]\n***[[Yupik peoples|Yupik]]: [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Alutiiq people|Alutiiq]] (Sugpiat): [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Central Alaskan Yup'ik people|Central Alaskan Yup'ik]] (Yupiat/Yupiit): [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Cup'ik people|Cup'ik]] (Cupiit): [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Nunivak Cup'ig people|Cup'ig]]: [[Nunivak Island (Alaska)]], [[United States]]\n****[[Siberian Yupik people|Siberian Yupik]] of [[St. Lawrence Island]], [[Alaska]], [[United States]].\n***Inuit peoples: [[Canadian Arctic]] - [[Northwest Territories]], [[Nunavik]], [[Nunatsiavut]], [[Nunavut]]; [[Greenland]]; [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Greenlandic Inuit]]: [[Greenland]]\n*****[[Inughuit]]: North Greenland\n*****[[Kalaallit]]: West Greenland\n*****[[Tunumiit]]: East Greenland\n****[[Inupiat]] (I\u00f1upiat): Alaska's Arctic, [[Alaska North Slope|North Slope]] and boroughs and the [[Bering Strait]]\n*****[[Nunamiut]]: [[Interior Alaska]].\n****[[Inuit|Inuit people]] (Inuit): [[Canadian Arctic]]\n*****Eastern Canadian Inuit: East Canadian Arctic, East [[Nunavut]], [[Nunavik]], [[Nunatsiavut]]\n*****[[Inuvialuit|Western Canadian Inuit]] (Inuvialuit): West Canadian Arctic, [[Inuvialuit Settlement Region]], Arctic coast of [[Northwest Territories]], West [[Nunavut]]\n*[[M\u00e9tis people (Canada)|M\u00e9tis]]: a mixed [[First Nations]] (from several peoples) and [[European peoples|European]] (from several peoples) people of [[Canada]].\n\n==== Subarctic ====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Subarctic}}\n\n*Na-Den\u00e9 peoples\n**Athabaskan peoples\n***Northern Athabaskan peoples\n****[[Dene]] of [[Yukon]], [[British Columbia]], [[Manitoba]], [[Northwest Territory]], and [[Alberta]], [[Canada]].\n****[[Alaskan Athabaskans]]\n*****Southern Alaskan peoples\n******[[Ahtna people|Ahtna]]\n******[[Ingalik]]\n*****[[Koyukon people|Koyukon]] of [[Interior Alaska]].\n*****[[Kutchin]] of [[Interior Alaska]] and the [[Yukon]].\n*****[[Tanana Athabaskans]].\n*****[[Upper Kuskokwim people|Kolchan]] of [[Interior Alaska]].\n*****[[Deg Hit'an]] of [[Interior Alaska]].\n*****[[Dena'ina]] of [[Interior Alaska]].\n*****[[Holikachuk people|Holikachuk]]\n*****[[H\u00e4n]] of [[Yukon]], [[Canada]], and [[Alaska]], [[United States]].\n*[[M\u00e9tis people (Canada)|M\u00e9tis]]: a mixed [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] (from several peoples) and [[European peoples|European]] (from several peoples) people of [[Canada]].\n*[[Algonquian languages|Algonquians]]\n**[[Cree]] of [[Montana]], [[United States]], and [[Manitoba]], [[Alberta]], and [[Saskatchewan]], [[Canada]].\n**[[Innu]] of Northeastern [[Quebec]], and Western [[Labrador]], [[Canada]].\n**[[Annishinabe]] of [[Quebec]], [[Ontario]], and [[Manitoba]], [[Canada]], as well as [[Kansas]], [[Michigan]], [[Minnesota]], [[Oklahoma]], and [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]].\n***[[Algonquin people|Algonquin]] of [[Quebec]], and [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n**[[Beothuk]] of [[Newfoundland]], [[Canada]].\n\n==== Pacific Northwest Coast ====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Pacific Northwest Coast}}\n\n*[[Makah people|Makah]] of [[Washington (state)|Washington]], [[United States]].\n*[[Quinault people|Quinault]] of [[Washington (state)|Washington]], [[United States]].\n*[[Nuu-chah-nulth|Nootka]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]].\n*[[Kwakiutl]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]].\n*[[Eyak people|Eyak]] of [[Alaska]], [[United States]].\n*[[Haida people|Haida]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], and [[Alaska]], [[United States]].\n*[[Tlingit]] of [[Alaska]], [[United States]].\n*[[Tshimshian]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], and [[Alaska]], [[United States]].\n\n==== Northwest Plateau-Great Basin-California ====\n===== Northwest Plateau =====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Northwest Plateau}}\n\n===== Great Basin =====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Great Basin}}\n\n*[[Ute people|Ute]] of [[Utah]], [[United States]].\n*[[Shoshone]] of [[Colorado]], [[Nevada]], and [[Utah]], [[United States]].\n**[[Mono people|Mono]] of [[California]], [[United States]].\n**[[Bannock people|Bannock]] of [[Idaho]], [[United States]].\n**[[Western Shoshon