[[United States]].\n**[[Ohlone people|Ohlone]] of [[California]], [[United States]].\n*[[Karok people|Karok]] of [[California]], [[United States]].\n\n==== Great Plains ====\n{{Main|Plains Indians}}\n\n*[[Comanche]] of [[Texas]] and [[Oklahoma]], [[United States]].\n*[[Osage Nation|Osage]] of [[Kansas]] and [[Nebraska]], [[United States]].\n*[[Sioux]] of [[North Dakota]], [[South Dakota]], and [[Minnesota]], [[United States]], as well as [[Saskatchewan]], and [[Alberta]], [[Canada]].\n**[[Lakota people|Lakota]] of [[South Dakota]], [[United States]].\n**[[Dakota people]] of [[Minnesota]], [[United States]], and [[Saskatchewan]], [[Canada]].\n*[[Kiowa]] of [[Texas]], and [[Oklahoma]].\n**[[Plains Apache]] (see the Southwest section for another category this tribe belongs too) of [[Texas]], and [[Oklahoma]].\n*[[Crow people|Crow]] of [[Montana]].\n*[[Omaha people|Omaha]] of [[Nebraska]].\n*[[Blackfoot]] of [[Montana]], [[United States]], and [[Saskatchewan]], [[Canada]].\n\n==== Eastern Woodlands ====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Eastern Woodlands}}\n\n===== Northeastern Woodlands =====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Northeastern Woodlands}}\n\n*[[Iroquoian languages|Iroquoian]] peoples\n**[[Haudenosaunee]] of [[New York (state)|New York]], [[Wisconsin]], and [[Oklahoma]], [[United States]], as well as [[Quebec]] and [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n***[[Mohawk people|Mohawk]] of [[Quebec]], [[Canada]], and [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States]].\n***[[Seneca people|Seneca]] of [[New York (state)|New York]], and Oklahoma, [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n***[[Cayuga people|Cayuga]] of [[Oklahoma]], and [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n***[[Oneida people|Oneida]] of [[Wisconsin]] and [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n***[[Tuscarora people|Tuscarora]] of [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States]], and [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n***[[Onondaga people|Onondaga]] of [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States]], and [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n**[[Wyandot people|Wyandot]] of [[Kansas]], [[Michigan]], and [[Oklahoma]], [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n**''[[Erie people|Nation du chat]]'' of [[Upstate New York]], [[Ohio]], and Northwest [[Pennsylvania]], [[United States]].\n**[[Susquehannock]] of [[Pennsylvania]], and [[West Virginia]], [[United States]].\n**[[St. Lawrence Iroquoians]]: [[St. Lawrence River]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]], and [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States]].\n**[[Monongahela culture|Monongahela]]: [[Pennsylvania]], [[West Virginia]], and [[Ohio]], [[United States]].\n**[[Nottoway people|Nottoway]] of [[Virginia]], [[United States]].\n**[[Westo]] of [[Virginia]] and [[South Carolina]], [[United States]].\n*[[Algic languages|Algic]] peoples\n**[[Algonquian peoples]]\n***[[Chowanoke]] of [[North Carolina]].\n***Carolina Algonquian\n****[[Roanoke tribe|Roanoke]] of [[North Carolina]].\n*****[[Croatan]] of [[North Carolina]].\n***[[Powhatan Confederacy]] of [[Virginia]].\n****[[Pamunkey]] of [[Virginia]], [[United States]].\n****[[Powhatan people]] of [[Virginia]], [[United States]].\n***[[Wampanoag people|Wampanoag]] of [[Massachusetts]].\n***[[Wabanaki Confederacy|Wabanaki]] of [[Maine]], [[United States]], and [[New Brunswick]] and [[Newfoundland]], [[Canada]].\n****[[Abenaki]] of [[New Hampshire]], [[Maine]] and [[Vermont]].\n****[[Penobscot]] of [[Maine]].\n****[[Miqmac]] of [[New Brunswick]], and [[Newfoundland]].\n****[[Passamaquoddy]] of [[Maine]], [[United States]], and [[New Brunswick]], [[Canada]].\n****[[Maliseet]] of [[New Brunswick]] and [[Quebec]].\n***[[Shawnee]] of the [[Ohio River Valley]], now [[Oklahoma]].\n***[[Central Algonquian]] peoples\n****[[Kickapoo people|Kikap\u00fa]] ([[Kickapoo people|Kiikaapoa]]/[[Kickapoo people|Kiikaapoi]]): indigenous from southeast [[Michigan]], [[United States]], also in [[Coahuila]], [[Mexico]]\n****[[Peoria tribe|Peoria]] (Illiniwek)\n****[[Annishinabe]]\n*****[[Ojibwe]] of [[Minnesota]], [[North Dakota]], and [[Michigan]], [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n*****[[Potawatomi]] of [[Michigan]] and [[Indiana]], [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n*****[[Odawa]] of [[Oklahoma]] and [[Michigan]], [[United States]], as well as [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].\n****[[Cree]] of [[Alberta]], [[Manitoba]], [[Ontario]], [[Saskatchewan]], and the [[Northwest Territories]], [[Canada]], as well as [[Montana]], [[United States]].\n\n===== Southeastern Woodlands =====\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples of the Southeastern Woodlands}}\n\n*[[Cherokee]] of [[North Carolina]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], and [[Oklahoma]].\n*[[Natchez people|Natchez]] of [[Louisiana]] and [[Arkansas]].\n*[[Muskogean languages|Muskogeans]]\n**[[Muscogee|Muskogee]] of [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], now [[Oklahoma]].\n**[[Choctaw]] of [[Louisiana]], [[Alabama]], and [[Oklahoma]].\n**[[Chickasaw]] of [[Tennessee]], now [[Oklahoma]].\n*[[Indigenous peoples of Florida]]\n**[[Indigenous people of the Everglades region]]\n***[[Calusa]] of South [[Florida]].\n***[[Tequesta]] of South [[Florida]].\n**[[Timucua]] of Northern [[Florida]] and Southern [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].\n**[[Apalachee]] of the [[Florida Panhandle]] and [[Alabama]].\n**[[Seminole]] of [[Oklahoma]], and [[Florida]].\n*[[Siouan languages|Siouans]]\n**[[Ho-Chunk]] of [[Wisconsin]] and [[Michigan]].\n**[[Catawba people|Catawba]] of [[North Carolina]].\n**[[Pee Dee people|Pee Dee]] of [[South Carolina]].\n*[[Caddoan languages|Caddoans]]\n**[[Caddo]] of [[Texas]], [[Arkansas]], and [[Louisiana]].\n**[[Pawnee people|Pawnee]] of [[Oklahoma]] and [[Arkansas]], [[United States]].\n**[[Southern Plains villagers]] of Western [[Oklahoma]], [[Texas]], [[Kansas]], and Southeastern [[Colorado]].\n**[[Arikara]] of [[North Dakota]], [[United States]].\n**[[Hidatsa]] of [[North Dakota]], [[United States]].\n**[[Wichita people|Wichita]] of [[Oklahoma]], [[Kansas]], and [[Texas]], [[United States]].\n\n==== Southwest ====\n{{Main|Southwest peoples}}\n\n*[[Uto-Aztecan]] peoples\n**[[Aztecan languages|Aztecan]] ([[Nahuan languages|Nahuan]]) peoples\n***[[Mexicanero]] (M\u0113xihcah): [[Durango]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[C\u00e1hita language|C\u00e1hita]]n peoples\n***[[Yaqui people|Yaqui]] (Hiaki/Yoeme): [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]], and [[Arizona]], [[United States]].\n***[[Mayo people|Mayo]] (Yoreme): [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Tarahumaran languages|Tarahumaran]] peoples\n***[[Guarij\u00edo]]: [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Tarahumara]] (Rar\u00e1muri-Omug\u00ed): [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] and [[Durango]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Tepiman languages|Tepiman]] peoples\n***[[Pima Bajo]]: [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Tepehu\u00e1n]] (O'dam/Audam/\u00d3dami): [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] and [[Durango]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Seri people|Seri]] (Comcaac): [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Puebloan peoples]]: [[Colorado]], [[New Mexico]], [[Arizona]], [[Utah]], and [[Texas]], [[United States]]\n**[[Hopi]] of [[New Mexico]], [[United States]].\n**[[Zuni people|Zuni]] of [[Arizona]], [[United States]].\n**[[Anasazi]] of [[New Mexico]] and [[Colorado]], [[United States]].\n**[[Tiwa people|Tiwa]] of [[New Mexico]], [[United States]].\n**[[Mogollon culture|Mogollon]] of [[New Mexico]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]], and [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]].\n**[[Hohokam]] of Southern [[Arizona]], [[United States]].\n*[[Southern Athabascan]]s\n**[[Apache]] of [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]], [[Coahuilla]], and [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]], as well as [[Arizona]], [[New Mexico]], [[Oklahoma]], and [[Texas]], [[United States]].\n***[[Chiricahua]] of Southern [[New Mexico]], [[Northern Mexico]], and Southeast [[Arizona]].\n***[[Lipan Apache]] of Northern [[Texas]], and [[Western Oklahoma]].\n***[[Plains Apache]] of [[Oklahoma]].\n***[[Mescalero]] of [[Arizona]], [[New Mexico]], and Northern [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]].\n***[[Western Apache]] of Western [[Arizona]].\n**[[Navajo]] of the [[Four Corners]] region.\n*[[O'odham]] of [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]], and [[Arizona]], [[United States]].\n**[[Pima people|Pima]] of [[Arizona]], [[United States]].\n**[[Tohono O'odham people|Papago]] of far Northern [[Sonora]], [[Mexico]], and Southern [[Arizona]], [[United States]].\n\n==== Mesoamerica ====\n[[File:DancersMuniPalaceSanCris2.JPG|thumb|[[Tzeltal people|Tzeltal]] dancers waiting to perform, [[San Crist\u00f3bal de las Casas|San Cristobal]].]]\n[[File:Mam people.jpg|thumb|[[Mam people|Mam]] people.]]\n[[File:Tunkan Maia Yucatan.jpg|thumb| [[Maya peoples|Mayan]] family from [[Yucat\u00e1n]]]]\n[[File:GFProcessionXochis05.JPG|thumb|[[Amuzgo people|Amuzgos]] in traditional dress.]]\n[[File:Huautla de Jimenez.jpg|thumb|[[Mazatec people|Mazatec]] girls performing a dance in [[Huautla de Jimenez]].]]\n[[File:Huichol indian.jpg|thumb|[[Huichol people|Huichol]] woman and child.]]\n\n*[[Huave people|Huave]] ([[Huave people|Ikoots]]/[[Huave people|Kunajts]]): [[Oaxaca]], Mexico\n*[[Lenca people|Lenca]]: [[Honduras]] and [[El Salvador]]\n*[[Maya peoples]]\n**[[Ch'olan languages|Ch'olan]] peoples\n***[[Ch'ol people|Ch'ol]]: [[Chiapas]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Ch'orti' people|Ch'orti']]: [[El Salvador]]\n***[[Chontal Maya people|Chontal Maya]] (Yokot'anob/Yokot'an): [[Tabasco]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Tzeltal people|Tzeltal]] (Winik Atel/Batzil\u02bcop): [[Chiapas]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Tzotzil people|Tzotzil]] (Bats'ik'op]]/Sotz'leb): [[Chiapas]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Huastec people|Huastec]] (T\u00e9enek/Te' Inik): [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Mamean languages|Mamean]] peoples\n***[[Ixil people|Ixil]]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Mam people|Mam]]: [[Guatemala]]\n**[[Q'anjobalan languages|Q'anjobalan]] peoples\n***[[Chuj people|Chuj]]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Jakaltek people|Jakaltek]]: [[Guatemala]]&nbsp;\u2013 also called Popt\u00ed\n***[[Q'anjob'al people|Q'anjob'al]]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Tojolabal]]: [[Guatemala]]\n**Qichean peoples\n***[[Achi people|Achi']]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Kaqchikel people|Kaqchikel]]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[K'iche' people|K'iche']]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Poqomchi']]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Poqomam people|Poqomam]]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Q'eqchi' people|Q'eqchi']]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Tz'utujil people|Tz'utujil]]: [[Guatemala]]\n**[[Yucatecan languages|Yucatecan]] peoples\n***[[Itza]]: [[Guatemala]]\n***[[Lacandon people|Lacand\u00f3n]] (Hach Winik): [[Chiapas]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Mopan people|Mopan]]: [[Guatemala]] and [[Belize]]\n***[[Yucatec Maya]] (Maya proper) (M\u00e0aya): [[Yucat\u00e1n (state)|Yucat\u00e1n]], [[Quintana Roo]] and [[Campeche]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Mixe-Zoquean languages|Mixe-Zoquean]] peoples\n**[[Mixe people|Mixe]] (Ay\u00fc\u00fckj\u00e4'\u00e4y): [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Zoque people|Zoque]]: [[Oaxaca]] and [[Chiapas]] [[Mexico]]\n*[[Oto-Manguean]] peoples\n**[[Amuzgo people|Amuzgo]] (Tzjon Non/Tzo'tyio/\u00d1'anncue): [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Chinantec]]: [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Manguean languages|Manguean]]\n***[[Chorotega people|Chorotega]] (Mangue/Mankeme): [[Honduras]], [[Nicaragua]], and [[Costa Rica]]\n**[[Mixtecan languages|Mixtecan]]\n***[[Cuicatec]]:[[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Mixtec]] (\u00d1u\u00f9 Savi/Nay\u00edvi Savi/\u00d1u\u00f9 Davi/Nayivi Davi): [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Trique people|Trique]]: [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Oto-Pamean languages|Oto-Pamean]] peoples\n***[[Chichimeca Jonaz]] ([[Chichimeca Jonaz people|\u00daza]]): [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Matlatzinca people|Matlatzinca]]: [[Mexico (state)]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Mazahua people|Mazahua]] (Tetjo \u00d1aa J\u00f1atjo): [[Mexico (state)]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Otomi people|Otomi]] (H\u00f1\u00e4h\u00f1u/H\u00f1\u00e4h\u00f1o/\u00d1uhu/\u00d1hato/\u00d1uhmu): [[Central Mexico]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Pame people|Pame]] (Xi'\u00fai): [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Popolocan languages|Popolocan]] peoples\n***[[Chochotec|Chocho]] (Ngiwa): [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Ixcatec]]: [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Popoloca]]: [[Oaxaca]], and [[Puebla]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Mazatec people|Mazatec]] (Ha Shuta Enima): [[Puebla]] and [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Tlapanec people|Tlapanec]] (Me'phaa): [[Guerrero]], [[Mexico]]\n**[[Zapotec peoples|Zapotecan peoples]]\n***[[Chatino]] (Kitse Cha't\u00f1o): [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Zapotec people|Zapotec]] (Be'ena'a/Didxa\u017eon): [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Pur\u00e9pecha people|Tarascan]] (P'urh\u00e9pecha): [[Michoac\u00e1n]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Tequistlatecan]]/[[Tequistlatecan|Chontal de Oaxaca]]: [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Totonacan]] peoples\n**[[Totonac]] (Tutunacu): [[Veracruz]] and [[Puebla]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Uto-Aztecan]] peoples\n**[[Aztecan languages|Aztecan]] peoples\n***[[Nahua People|Nahua]] (N\u0101huatl\u0101cah): [[Mexico]]\n**Corachol peoples\n***[[Cora People|Cora]] (N\u00e1ayarite): [[Jalisco]] and [[Nayarit]], [[Mexico]]\n***[[Huichol people|Huichol]] (Wix\u00e1ritari/Wix\u00e1rita): [[Jalisco]] and [[Nayarit]], [[Mexico]]\n*[[Xinca people|Xinca]] (Xinka): [[Guatemala]]\n\n==== Circum-Caribbean ====\n[[File:Panama-Kuna 0610a.jpg|thumb|A [[Kuna people|Kuna]] woman in traditional dress.]]\n[[File:Garifuna Umalali.jpg|thumb|[[Umalali|Umalali featuring the Garifuna Collective]] on the Peace Corps World Stage at [[Smithsonian Folklife Festival]] 2011]]\n\n*[[Chibchan languages|Chibchan]] peoples\n**[[Boruca people|Boruca]]: [[Costa Rica]]\n**[[Bribri people|Bribri]]: [[Costa Rica]]\n**[[Cab\u00e9car people|Cab\u00e9car]]: [[Costa Rica]]\n**[[Naso people|Naso]]/[[Teribe]]/[[Naso people|Tj\u00ebr Di]]: [[Costa Rica]], [[Panama]]\n**[[Guaym\u00ed language|Guaymi]]/Waimi peoples\n***[[Bokota people|Bokota]]: [[Panama]]\n***[[Ng\u00f6be\u2013Bugl\u00e9 people|Ng\u00e4be\u2013Bugl\u00e9]]: [[Panama]], Costa Rica\n***[[Talamanca languages|Talamanca]] peoplesl\n**[[Kuna (people)|Kuna]] ([[Kuna people|Dule]]/[[Kuna people|Tule]]): [[Panama]]\n**[[Pech people|Pech]]: [[Honduras]]\n**[[Votic languages|Votic]] peoples\n***[[Maleku people|Maleku]]: [[Costa Rica]]\n***[[Rama (people)|Rama]]: [[Nicaragua]]\n*[[Choc\u00f3 people|Choc\u00f3]]/[[Embera-Wounaan]] peoples\n**[[Ember\u00e1 people|Ember\u00e1]]/Choc\u00f3 proper ([[Ember\u00e1 people|\u025b\u0303ber\u00e1]]): [[Panama]]\n*[[Misumalpan]] peoples\n**[[Miskito people|Miskito]] ([[Miskito people|Miskitu]]): [[Honduras]] and [[Nicaragua]]\n***[[Tawira Miskito]] ([[Tawira Miskito|Tawira Miskitu]]) \n**[[Sumalpan]] peoples\n***[[Sumo (people)|Sumo]] ([[Sumo people|Mayangna]]): [[Nicaragua]]\n*[[Tolupan people|Tolupan]]/[[Jicaque people|Jicaque]]: [[Honduras]]\n*[[Zambo]]/[[Cafuso]] peoples (mixed [[West Africa]]n and [[Amerindian]] peoples)\n**[[Gar\u00edfuna]]: A mixed West African (from several peoples) and Amerindian people (mainly from the [[Island Caribs]] - Kalh\u00edphona) that traditionally speaks an [[Arawakan languages|Arawakan]] language in [[Belize]] and [[Honduras]].\n**[[Miskito Sambu]]: A mixed West African (from several peoples) and Amerindian people (mainly from the original Miskito) that traditionally speaks [[Miskito language|Miskito]], a Misumalpan language, and also [[Nicaragua Creole English]] in [[Nicaragua]] and [[Honduras]].\n*[[Black Seminoles]]: [[Florida]], [[The Bahamas]], and [[Mexico]]. (Mixed [[Seminole]] and [[African people|African]]).\n\n==== Caribbean ====\n[[File:Kalina Paris 1892.jpg|thumb|300px|Portrait of the Kali'na exhibited at the Jardin d'Acclimatation in Paris in 1892]]\n\nThe [[Caribbean]], or the [[West Indies]], generally includes the island chains of the [[Caribbean Sea]].\n\n*[[Arawak]]an peoples\n**Northern\n***[[Arawakan languages|Circum-Caribbean]]/[[Ta-Arawakan]] peoples\n****[[Eyeri]]/[[Igneri]]: [[Lesser Antilles]]. An [[Arawak people]], may have been the [[Kalinago]]/[[Island Caribs]] before caribbeanization. (The [[Island Caribs]] had the tradition that the [[Igneri]] were the older people of [[Lesser Antilles]] but they could have been ancestors of the majority of [[Island Caribs]]).\n****[[Island Caribs]] ([[Island Caribs|Carib]]/[[Kalinago]]/[[Kalina people|Kalh\u00edphona]]): [[Lesser Antilles]]. Often called \"[[Island Caribs]]\" (but may have been an older [[arawak people]] with a [[Kalina people|carib]] conquering warrior elite or influenced by [[Mainland Caribs]]. Apparently, the majority of the people spoke an [[arawakan language]] and not a carib one.)\n****[[Ta\u00edno people|Ta\u00edno]]: [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Amerindians]] who originally inhabited the [[Greater Antilles]] of the Caribbean, they are of [[Arawak people|Arawakan]] descent.\n*****[[Neo-Ta\u00edno nations]] Some scholars distinguish between the [[Ta\u00edno people|Ta\u00edno]] and Neo-Ta\u00edno groups. Neo-Ta\u00edno groups were also [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Amerindians]] of the Antilles islands, but had distinctive languages and cultural practices that differed from the ''High Ta\u00edno''.<ref>Rouse (1992)</ref> These groups include:\n******[[Ciboney]]: a term preferred in Cuban historical texts for the neo-Taino-Siboney nations of the island of Cuba.\n******[[Ciguayo]]: Eastern [[Hispaniola]]\n******[[Lucayans]]: Based in the [[Bahamas]].\n******[[Neo-Taino nations#Neo-Ta.C3.ADno nations and related ethnic groups|Macorix]]: [[Hispaniola]].\n*[[Guanahatabey|Guanahatabey people]]: Western [[Cuba]] island, a Pre-[[Arawakan people|Arawakan]] and Pre-[[Island Caribs|Island Carib]] people of the [[Caribbean Islands]].\n\n=== South America ===\n[[File:Mujeres de la etnia Ember\u00e1.jpg|thumb|[[Ember\u00e1 people|Ember\u00e1]] women]]\n[[File:Urarina shaman B Dean.jpg|thumb|[[Urarina]] [[shaman]], 1988]]\n[[File:Bororo004.jpg|250px|thumb|[[Boror\u00f3 people|Bororo]]-Boe man from Mato Grosso at Brazil's [[Indigenous Games]], 2007]]\n[[File:Pai Tavytera Indians.jpg|thumb|[[Pai Tavytera people]] in [[Amambay Department]], Paraguay, 2012]]\n[[File:Quechuawomanandchild.jpg|thumb|[[Quechua people|Quechua]] woman and child in the [[Sacred Valley]], Peru]]\n\n[[South America]] generally includes all of the continent and islands south of the [[Isthmus of Panama]].\n\n{{Main|Indigenous peoples in South America|List of Indigenous peoples of South America}}\n\n*[[Indigenous peoples in South America]] by Country:\n**[[Indigenous peoples in Argentina]]\n**[[List of indigenous peoples in Brazil]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples in Chile]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples in Colombia]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples in Ecuador]]\n**[[Indigenous peoples in Peru]]\n\n*[[Indigenous peoples in South America]] by native cultural regions\n\n==== Circum-Caribbean (Chibcha) ====\n*[[Arawakan languages|Arawakan]] peoples\n**Northern\n***[[Ta-Arawakan]]\n****[[Wayuu]]: [[Venezuela]]/[[Colombia]]\n*[[Chibchan]] peoples\n**Chibcha\u2013Motilon\n***Chibcha\u2013Tunebo\n****[[U'wa people|U'wa]]: [[Colombia]]\n**Kuna\u2013Colombian\n***[[Kuna people|Kuna]] ([[Kuna people|Dule]]/[[Kuna people|Tule]]): [[Panama]]\n*[[Chocoan]] peoples\n**[[Embera-Wounaan|Embera]] ([[Ember\u00e1 people|\u025b\u0303ber\u00e1]]): [[Colombia]]/[[Panam\u00e1]]\n*[[Warao people|Warao]]: [[Venezuela]]'s [[Orinoco River]] delta region.\n\n==== Amazon ====\n*[[Arawakan languages|Arawakan]] peoples\n**Southern\n***Campa\n****[[Ash\u00e1ninka]]: [[Peru]]\n*[[Barbacoan]] peoples\n**Awan\n***[[Awa-Kwaiker people|Aw\u00e1-Kwaiker]]: Northern Ecuador\n*[[Bora-Witoto]] peoples\n**[[Bora people|Bora]]: [[Colombia]]/[[Peru]]\n*Cahuapanan peoples\n**[[Chayahuita]]: [[Loreto Region|Loreto]], [[Peru]]\n*[[Jivaroan peoples|Jivaroan]] ([[Jivaroan peoples|Shuar]]): [[Loreto Region|Loreto]] and [[San Mart\u00edn Region|San Mart\u00edn]], [[Peru]]\n*[[Nukak]]: [[Colombia]]\n*[[Panoan]] peoples\n**Mainline Panoan\n***Nawa\n****Chama\n*****[[Shipibo-Conibo people]]: [[Ucayali Region|Ucayali]], [[Peru]]\n******[[Shipibo]]: [[Ucayali Region|Ucayali]], [[Peru]]\n****Headwaters\n*****[[Yora]]: [[Amazon rainforest]], southeast [[Peru]]\n**Mayoruna\n***Mayo\n****[[Korubu]] ([[Dslala]]): [[Brazil]]\n****[[Matis]]: [[Brazil]]/[[Peru]]\n****[[Mats\u00e9s]]: [[Brazil]]/[[Peru]]\n*[[Ticuna-Yuri languages|Ticuna-Yuri]] peoples\n**[[Ticuna people|Ticuna]] ([[Ticuna people|Tikuna]]): [[Brazil]]/[[Peru]]/[[Colombia]]\n*[[Tucanoan]] peoples\n**Eastern\n***North\n****[[Tukano]]: [[Colombia]]\n**Western\n***Napo\n****Siona\u2013Secoya\n*****[[Secoya people|Secoya]]: [[Loreto Region|Loreto]], [[Peru]]/[[Ecuador]]\n*[[Tupian]] peoples\n**[[Tup\u00ed-Guaran\u00ed]]\n***[[Tupi people|Tupi]]: [[Paraguay]], [[Brazil]], [[Bolivia]], [[Peru]] and [[Argentina]]\n****Cocama-Omagua\n*****[[Cocama-Cocamilla]] ([[Cocama-Cocamilla|Kok\u00e1ma]]): [[Loreto Region|Loreto]], [[Peru]]\n***[[Tapirap\u00e9 people|Tapirape]]: [[Brazil]]\n***Wayamp\u00ed\n****Guaj\u00e1\n*****[[Aw\u00e1-Guaj\u00e1 people|Aw\u00e1-Guaj\u00e1]]: eastern [[Amazon rainforest|Amazonian rainforest]], [[Brazil]]\n*[[Urarina]] ([[Kach\u00e1]]): [[Chambira Basin]], [[Loreto Region|Loreto]] [[Peru]]\n*[[Yanomami]] ([[Yanomami people|Yan\u00f5mami]]/[[Yanomami people|Yan\u00f5mami Th\u00ebp\u00eb]]): [[Venezuela]]/[[Brazil]]\n\n===== Guianas =====\n*[[Cariban]] peoples\n**[[Galibi]]/[[Kalina people|Kalina]] ([[Mainland Caribs]]): [[Guianas]], [[Venezuela]] (northern coast of South America)\n**Yekuana\n**E\u00f1apa (Panare)\n**Pem\u00f3ng\n***Pem\u00f3ng\n***[[Makuxi]]: [[Brazil]], [[Guyana]]\n*[[Yanomami]] ([[Yanomami people|Yan\u00f5mami]]/[[Yanomami people|Yan\u00f5mami Th\u00ebp\u00eb]]): [[Venezuela]]/[[Brazil]]\n*[[Piaroa people|Piaroa]] (Woth\u00efha): Venezuela/Colombia\n\n==== Eastern Highlands (Brazilian Highlands) ====\n*Charruan peoples\n**[[Charr\u00faa]]: [[Uruguay]], [[Brazil]] and [[Argentina]]\n*[[Macro-G\u00ea]] peoples\n**Bororoan\n***[[Boror\u00f3 people|Bororo]]: [[Mato Grosso]], [[Brazil]]\n**Ofaie\n***[[Karaj\u00e1 people|Karaj\u00e1]]/[[Karaj\u00e1 people|Iny]]: [[Brazil]]\n*[[Tupian]] peoples\n**[[Tup\u00ed-Guaran\u00ed]]\n***[[Guaran\u00ed (I)]]\n****[[Ach\u00e9|Ache]]: [[Paraguay]]\n****[[Pai Tavytera people|Pai Tavytera]]: [[Paraguay]]\n****Guaran\u00ed\n*****[[Guarani people|Guaran\u00ed]] ([[Guaran\u00ed people|Ab\u00e1]]/[[Guaran\u00ed people|Av\u00e1]]): [[Paraguay]], [[Uruguay]], [[Brazil]], [[Bolivia]] and [[Argentina]]\n***[[Tupi people|Tupi]]: [[Paraguay]], [[Brazil]], [[Bolivia]], [[Peru]] and [[Argentina]]\n****Cocama-Omagua\n*****[[Cocama-Cocamilla]] ([[Cocama-Cocamilla|Kok\u00e1ma]]): [[Loreto Region|Loreto]], [[Peru]]\n***[[Tapirap\u00e9 people|Tapirape]]: [[Brazil]]\n***Wayamp\u00ed\n****Guaj\u00e1\n*****[[Aw\u00e1-Guaj\u00e1 people|Aw\u00e1-Guaj\u00e1]]: eastern [[Amazon rainforest|Amazonian rainforest]], [[Brazil]]\n\n==== Chaco ====\n*[[Mascoian]] peoples\n**[[Enxet]]: [[Paraguay]]\n*[[Matacoan]] peoples\n**[[Wich\u00ed people|Wich\u00ed]]: the [[Gran Chaco|Chaco]], [[Argentina]]/[[Bolivia]]\n*[[Zamucoan]] peoples\n**[[Ayoreo people|Ayoreo]]: the [[Gran Chaco|Chaco]], [[Paraguay]]/[[Bolivia]]\n\n==== Central Andes ====\n*[[Aymaran languages|Aymaran]] peoples\n**[[Aymara people|Aymara]]: [[Peru]]/[[Bolivia]]/[[Chile]]\n*[[P\u00e1ez people|Nasa]]: [[Colombia]]\n*[[Quechua people|Quechuan peoples]]\n**[[Quechua people|Quechua]] ([[Quechua people|Nunakuna]]/[[Quechua people|Runakuna]]/[[Quechua people|Kichwa]]/[[Quechua people|Inga]])\n\n==== Southern Cone ====\n===== Araucania =====\n*[[Araucanian]] peoples\n**[[Mapuche]] ([[Araucanians]]): [[Chile]]/[[Argentina]]\n**[[Huilliche people|Mapuche-Huilliche]]\n**[[Pehuenche]]\n\n===== Patagonia =====\n===== Fire Land (Tierra del Fuego) =====\n*[[Alacalufe]] ([[Kaw\u00e9sqar people|Kaw\u00e9sqar]]): Far Southern [[Chile]]\n*[[Yaghan people|Yaghan]] ([[Yaghan people|Y\u00e1mana]]): Far Southern [[Chile]]\n\n== Oceania ==\n[[Oceania]] includes most islands of the Pacific Ocean, [[New Guinea]], [[New Zealand]] and the continent of [[Australia (continent)|Australia]].\n\nList of peoples by geographical and ethnolinguistic grouping:\n\n=== Australia ===\n[[File:Aboriginal farmers at Franklinford 1858.jpg|thumb|Aboriginal farmers in Victoria, Australia, 1858]]\n[[Indigenous Australians]] include [[Aboriginal Australians]] on the [[Australia (continent)|mainland]] and [[Tiwi Islands]] as well as [[Torres Strait Islander]] peoples from the [[Torres Strait Islands]].\n\n*Aboriginal Australians include [[List of Australian Aboriginal group names|hundreds of groupings]] of people, defined by various overlapping characteristics such as language, culture and geography, which may include sub-groups. The [[Aboriginal Tasmanians|Indigenous peoples of the island state of Tasmania]] and the [[Tiwi people]] (of the [[Tiwi Islands]] off the [[Northern Territory]]) are also Aboriginal peoples, who are genetically and culturally distinct from Torres Strait Islander peoples.\n\n*Torres Strait Islander peoples are culturally and linguistically [[New Guinea|Papuo]]-[[Austronesian]], and the various peoples of the islands are of predominantly [[Melanesian]] descent. The [[Torres Strait Islands]] are part of the state of [[Queensland]].\n\n=== Melanesia ===\n[[File:Music show in Fiji.jpg|thumb|Fijians.]]\n[[Melanesia]] generally includes [[New Guinea]] and other (far-)western Pacific islands from the [[Arafura Sea]] out to [[Fiji]]. The region is mostly inhabited by the [[Melanesians|Melanesian]] peoples.\n\n*[[Melanesians]]\n**[[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] speaking Melanesians\n***[[Fijians]] (iTaukei): [[Fiji]]\n***[[Kanak people|Kanak]]: [[New-Caledonia]]\n***[[Malaita|Malaitan people]]: [[Malaita]], [[Solomon Islands]]\n***[[Ni-Vanuatu]]: [[Vanuatu]]\n**[[Papuan languages|Papuan]] speaking Melanesians\n***[[Baining people|Baining]]\n*[[Papuans]]: more than 250 distinct [[tribe]]s or clans, each with their own language and culture. The main island of [[New Guinea]] and surrounding islands (territory forming independent state of [[Papua New Guinea]] (PNG) and the [[Indonesia]]n provinces of [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]] and [[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]]. Considered \"Indigenous\" these people are a subject to many debates.\n**[[Sepik languages|Sepik]] peoples\n***[[Kwoma people|Kwoma]]: [[Peilungua Mountains]], [[Papua New Guinea]].\n***[[Iatmul people|Iatmul]]: [[Sepik]], [[Papua New Guinea]].\n***Sepik Hill\n****Sanio\n*****[[Hewa people|Hewa]]: Southern Highlands, PNG\n**[[Trans New Guinea languages|Trans New-Guinean]] peoples\n***[[Huli people|Huli]] of the [[Southern Highlands Province|Southern Highlands]], [[Papua New Guinea]].\n***[[Angu]]: Southwestern [[Morobe Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]].\n***Bosavi\n****Kaluli-Kasua\n*****[[Kaluli people|Kaluli]]: [[Great Papuan Plateau]], PNG\n***Ok\n****Mountain Ok\n*****[[Wopkaimin people|Wopkaimin]]: western PNG, [[Star Mountains]].\n***[[West Trans-New Guinea languages|West Trans New-Guinean]] peoples\n****[[Dani people|Dani]]: [[Papua (province)|Papua]], [[Indonesia]]\n****[[Korowai people|Korowai]]: [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]], close to the [[Papua New Guinea]] border.\n****[[Asmat people|Asmat]]: [[Asmat Regency]], [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]].\n\n=== Micronesia ===\n[[Micronesia]] generally includes the various small island chains of the western and central Pacific. The region is mostly inhabited by the [[Micronesia]]n peoples.\n\n*[[Micronesian people|Micronesians]]\n**[[Chamorros]]: [[Northern Marianas]] and [[Guam]]\n**[[Carolinians]]: [[Northern Marianas]]\n\n=== Polynesia ===\n[[File:Samoa Familie.JPG|thumb|[[Samoans|Samoan]] family]]\n[[Polynesia]] includes New Zealand and the islands of the central and southern Pacific Ocean. The region is mostly inhabited by the [[Polynesians|Polynesian]] peoples.\n\n*[[Polynesians]]\n**Ellicean\u2013Outlier\n***[[Tuvaluan people]]: [[Tuvalu]]\n**Futunic\n***[[Wallis (island)|Uvea]] and [[Futuna (Wallis and Futuna)|Futuna]]:[[Wallis and Futuna]]\n**Marquesic\n***[[Native Hawaiians|Kanaka Maoli]]: [[Hawaii]], [[United States]]\n***Marquesan and Mangarevan\n****[[Gambier Islands|Mangareva]]: [[Gambier Islands]]\n****[[Marquesas Islands|Marquesas Islanders]]: [[Marquesas Islands]]\n**[[Rapanui]]: [[Easter Island]] (Rapanui)\n**Samoic\n***[[Samoans]] (Tagata M\u0101o\u02bbi): [[Samoa]], [[American Samoa]]\n***[[Tokelau language|Tokelau]]: [[Tokelau]]\n**Tahitic\n***[[Austral Islands|Austral Islanders]]: [[Austral Islands]]\n***[[Cook Islanders|Cook Islands M\u0101ori]]: [[Cook Islands]]\n***[[Maohi]]: [[Tahiti]]\n***[[M\u0101ori people|M\u0101ori]]: [[Aotearoa]], [[New Zealand]]\n***[[Moriori people|Moriori]]: [[Chatham Islands]] (R\u0113kohu)\n***[[Tahitians]] (Ta'ata Tahiti (Ma'ohi)) : [[Tahiti]], [[French Polynesia]]\n***[[Tuamotus|Tuamotu]]: [[Tuamotus|Tuamotu Archipelago]]\n**Tongic\n***[[Niueans]]: [[Niue]]\n***[[Tongan people|Tongans]]: [[Tonga]]\n\n[[Polynesian outlier|Polynesian outliers]]\n*[[Polynesians]]\n**Ellicean\u2013Outlier\n***[[Kapingamarangi]] and [[Nukuoro]]: [[The Federated States of Micronesia]]\n***[[Nuguria]] [[Papua New Guinea]]\n***[[Nukumanu]] [[Papua New Guinea]]\n***[[Takuu]]: [[Papua New Guinea]]\n***[[Ontong Java]]\n***[[Sikaiana]]\n**Futunic\n***[[Anuta]]: [[Solomon Islands]]\n***[[Fagauvea]]: [[Ouv\u00e9a]] ([[New Caledonia]])\n***[[Futuna Island, Vanuatu|Futuna]] and [[Aniwa Island|Aniwa]]: [[Vanuatu]]\n****[[Futuna Island, Vanuatu|Futuna]]\n****[[Aniwa Island|Aniwa]]\n***[[Emae]]: [[Vanuatu]]\n***Makata: [[Vanuatu]]\n***[[Mele (island)|Mele]] (Erakoro, Eratapu): [[Vanuatu]]\n***[[Rennel]] and [[Bellona Island|Bellona]]: [[Solomon Islands]]\n****[[Bellona Island|Bellona]]\n****[[Rennel]]\n***[[Tikopia]]: [[Solomon Islands]]\n***[[Vaeakau-Taumako]]: [[Solomon Islands]]\n\n== Circumpolar ==\n[[Circumpolar peoples]] is an umbrella term for the various indigenous peoples of the [[Arctic]].\nList of peoples by ethnolinguistic grouping:  \n\n*\"[[Paleosiberian languages|Paleosiberian]]\"\n**[[Chukotko-Kamchatkan peoples|Chukotko-Kamchatkan]]\n***[[Chukchi people|Chukchi]] (Lyg'oravetl'et/O'ravetl'et): [[Siberia]], [[Russian Far East]], [[Russia]]\n***[[Koryaks]] (Nymylan-Chauchuven): [[Russian Far East]]\n**[[Tungusic peoples|Tungusic]]\n***[[Evenks]] (Evenkil): [[China]], [[Mongolia]], [[Russia]]\n*[[Eskimo\u2013Aleut]]\n**[[Aleut]] (Unangax): [[Aleutian Islands]] and [[Kamchatka Krai]]\n**[[Eskimo peoples|Eskimo]]/Yupik-Inuit\n***[[Yupik peoples|Yupik]]: [[Alaska]], [[United States]] and the [[Russian Far East]], [[Siberia]]\n****[[Alutiiq people|Alutiiq]] (Sugpiat): [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Yup'ik]] (Yupiat/Yupiit/Cup'ik/Cupiit): [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Cup'ig]] (Nunivak Cup'ig people): [[Nunivak Island (Alaska)]], [[United States]]\n****[[Siberian Yupik people|Siberian Yupik]] (Yupighyt): Siberia, Russia\n***[[Inuit]]: [[Greenland]], Northern Canada ([[Nunavut]] and [[Northwest Territories]]), [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n****[[Inupiat people|Inupiat]] (I\u00f1upiat): Alaska's Arctic and [[Alaska North Slope|North Slope]] boroughs and the [[Bering Straits]]\n****[[Kalaallit]] ([[Kalaallit]]): [[Greenland]]\n*[[Turkic peoples|Turkic]]\n**Northeast Turks\n***[[Dolgans]] (Dolgan/Tya Kikhi): [[Siberia]] ([[Krasnoyarsk Krai]]), [[Russia]]\n***[[Yakuts]] (Sakha): [[Siberia]] ([[Sakha Republic]]), [[Russia]]\n*[[Finno-Ugric]]\n**[[Ugrians]], Yugra, Siberia, Russia\n***[[Khanty people|Khanty]] (Kantek/Khanti): [[Yugra]], [[Siberia]], [[Russia]]\n***[[Mansi people|Mansi]], formerly known as [[Voguls]]: [[Yugra]], [[Siberia]], [[Russia]]\n**[[Sami people|Sami]] (S\u00e1mi/Saami/Lapp), formerly known by the [[exonym]] [[Lapps]]: Northern Norway, Sweden, Finland, and [[Kola Peninsula]] in Russia\n*[[Samoyedic peoples]]\n**Northern Samoyedic peoples: [[Siberia|West Siberia]] and Far Northern [[European Russia]]\n***[[Enets people|Enets]] (Entsi): Far Northern [[Siberia|Western Siberia]], Russia\n***[[Nenets people|Nenets]] (Neney Neneche): Far Northern [[Siberia|Western Siberia]] and Far Northern [[European Russia]]\n***[[Nganasan people|Nganasan]] (\u014a\u0259n\u0259hsa(n\u0259h)): [[Taymyr Peninsula]], [[Siberia]], Russia\n*[[Yukaghirs]] (Odul/Vadul/Detkil'): Far Northern [[East Siberia]], Russia\n\n== See also ==\n{{Commons category|Indigenous people}}\n{{Wikisource|Draft United Nations Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples}}\n{{Wikisource|Convention concerning Indigenous and Tribal Peoples in Independent Countries}}\n\n*[[Center for World Indigenous Studies]]\n*[[Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples]]\n*[[Definitions and identity of indigenous peoples]]\n*[[Indigenous archaeology]]\n*[[Indigenous Dialogues]]\n*[[Indigenous (ecology)]]\n*[[Indigenous intellectual property]]\n*[[Indigenous knowledge]]\n*[[Indigenous language]]\n*[[Indigenous medicine]]\n*[[Indigenous music]]\n*[[International Work Group for Indigenous Affairs]]\n*[[United Nations Permanent Forum on Indigenous Issues]]\n*[[World Council of Indigenous Peoples]]\n*[[Working Group on Indigenous Populations]]\n*[[List of contemporary ethnic groups]]\n*[[Lists of people by nationality]]\n*[[List of indigenous rights organizations]]\n\n:''See all pages that start with'' [[Special:PrefixIndex/indigenous peoples|indigenous people]] ''or''  [[Special:PrefixIndex/indigenous|indigenous]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{refbegin|indent=yes}}<!--BEGIN biblio format. If indent param. is used, Please use a colon (:) instead of asterisk (*) for bullet markers in the references list -->\n: {{Citation|author=Kipuri, Naomi|year=2007|chapter=Kenya|title=The Indigenous World 2007|chapter-url=http://www.iwgia.org/sw29940.asp|chapter-format=[[PDF]] online edition|editor=Sille Stidsen (compilation and ed.)|others=Marianne Wiben Jensen (Horn of Africa and East Africa regional ed.)|series=International Work Group for Indigenous Affairs yearbooks |issn=1024-0217|location=Copenhagen|publisher=[[IWGIA]], distributed by [[Transaction Publishers]]|pages=468\u2013476|isbn=978-87-91563-23-2|oclc=3098167